Not all heroes wear capes. In fact, many of them are currently helping those that need it the most. We're talking about health workers. Some have told eNCA that flattening the curve isn't easy. #Day11ofLockdown #21daysLockdownSouthAfrica #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The difficult work of delivering essential services during the COVID-19 pandemic has not been simple or easy, but health workers are doing their jobs with pride. "Flattening the curve" is easier said than done but health workers have said they are committed to helping during this crisis. READ: Number of SA health workers infected with COVID-19 About 4,000 health workers are expected to clock in long hours under dangerous conditions, tracing, testing, and screening potential COVID-19 cases. At the same time, they are balancing the responsibility of their work with the need to protect their loved ones. READ: Denosa calls for greater protection of nurses These heroes continue putting their lives on the line for each South African who needs it. But it all starts with ordinary citizens staying at home. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.